Description:
So easy to let out or to live in!
Here's an apartment with attitude! Fresh, bright, and airy it is visually appealing with its smart presentation, yet pleasingly low maintenance and relaxing - just what you want for a home or investment property. Part of a tranquil complex, it has the benefit of being on the ground floor and having a delightful sunny private courtyard. There's intercom entry, timber flooring, entrance hall, living room with panel heater, separate eat-in kitchen, 2 bedrooms with BIRs, bathroom with laundry facilities, and separate toilet. An undercover car space is on title, and the location is convenient to Ormond shops, cafes, trains, buses, reserves and recreation.
It's a beauty!
Jack Slater : 0430 283 724

Description:
King Of The Hill - 829sqm approx
Positioned at the top of Ormond Hill, this impressive period home conveys a wonderful family lifestyle with a sublime combination of traditional beauty and contemporary class. Impeccable rooms of remarkable magnitude and character underpin this timeless home where exquisite details such as lead light bay windows, high ornate ceilings and intricately detailed walls add classic style and elegance. Timber floors and an art nouveau archway introduce a formal lounge/dining domain with fireplace, extending through to an immaculate kitchen/meals area and family room. Graced with a north oriented rear yard, families will enjoy the plentiful space for recreation and entertaining, complemented by a stunning solar heated swimming pool. A generous master suite is privately zoned downstairs with a large robed area and an attached home office, accompanied by a spectacular bathroom with Murano glass pendant lighting, while upstairs an additional 4 robed bedrooms (additional master suite with WIR/ensuite and bay/city views) and a sizeable bathroom make this the perfect home for growing families. This unique offering is further enhanced by hydronic heating, evaporative cooling, alarm, shed and ample off street parking, matched by a premier McKinnon Secondary College zone location, close to Ormond station, Ormond Primary and parklands.
Insights: 5 Maud Street, Ormond VIC 3204 was last sold in 2020 and 8 other 5 bedroom house in Ormond have recently been sold.

Description:
Townhouse in Mckinnon Secondary Zone
Quality built with a flair for family innovation, this imposing near new 3 bedroom + study 3 bath residence strikes a chord of entertaining excellence. Built by Knight Building Group, this stunning abode features a stylish private living area, 2 study areas, huge main bedroom (fitted WIR & double shower en-suite), north facing open plan entertaining with streamlined stone kitchen (Bosch appliances) & stacker sliding doors to a tropical deck & garden. Flawless with its bamboo floors, Emporite doors, high ceilings & brilliant light, it boasts ducted heating/cooling, ceiling speakers, ducted vac, alarm video intercom, water tank & auto garage. In the McKinnon Sec College zone, walk to shops, bus & schools.

Description:
Sweeping Frontage & Multiple Possibilities
Broad and bathed in sun, this is the biggest and brightest opportunity on one of Ormond's leafiest and loveliest streets. Offering a total of 1030sqm/11086sqft beyond a sweeping 66'/20.12m frontage, this widely versatile property comes with a beautifully detailed five room solid-brick period home, a wide northerly rear orientation...and multiple possibilties.
Look to the proximity to Ormond's shopping, station and schools and explore the opportunity for development (subject to Council Approval) on this expansive site to capitalise on this fine residential location close to North Rd's bus-route and Glen Huntly Rd's cosmopolitan shopping. Alternatively, see the renovation rewards offered by this superbly solid brick home and renovate to create grand family living in grounds of estate-like proportions.
Beautifully sited on the block, this three bedroom home is offered in rare time-capsule condition with a wealth of period detail including lavish leadlight, lofty strapped ceilings and multiple fireplaces across a grandly proportioned floorplan - perfect for future extension. Bring your development vision, see the period promise...look through the leaves and find the potential on this tree-lined avenue.

Description:
Huge land, huge potential, extremely motivated vendors!!
Charmed with enchanting period detail, this Art Deco 2 bedroom + study clinker brick one of a pair has an abundance of warmth. Featuring double glazed windows, you'll enjoy the benefit of living close to Ormond shops, station and schools, without the noise.
Gorgeous with high intricate ceilings, picture rails and polished boards, this mesmerising beauty features a lovely main bedroom with fitted BIRs and large study, 2nd bedroom, spellbinding lounge (OFP) with double doors to the captivating dining room (tapestry brick OFP), porcelain bathroom, 80s kitchen with ample storage, laundry and 2nd toilet. The deep north facing rear garden (490sqm approx) features a bullnose verandah with caf blinds, and plenty of scope to extend.
A real gem, this endearing home boasts ducted heating, split system air conditioning, security doors, double glazed windows, water tank and stencil paved driveway to an auto garage and workshop. With service road entry, an easy walk to North Road shops, cafes, restaurants, Ormond station and the Monash Uni bus.

Description:
Stylishly Spacious with a Courtyard to go Wild
Brilliantly renovated to reflect today's stylish modern lifestyle, this ground floor 2 bedroom security apartment has the private use of a tropical courtyard sanctuary to entertain in. Bigger than most, this idyllic haven features a central hallway with good storage, 2 great size bedrooms (BIRs), north facing living area, snazzy kitchen with stainless steel appliances including dishwasher overlooking the fabulous courtyard and a radiant white bathroom with laundry taps.
Chic with timber floors and a new coat of paint, this enviable lifestyler features intercom entry, a split system air conditioner, a fully landscaped easy care courtyard with Bamboo screening & auto gates to carport. Situated between Packer Park and the North Road shops, cafes and restaurants, moments to train, bus and schools.

Description:
Brand New Grand Period Luxury In Lifestyle Location
Impressive proportions present a beautifully designed brand new lifestyle environment with this double-storey town residence enjoying a luxurious setting within the McKinnon Secondary College Zone, just minutes from Ormond train station, Wattle Reserve, Kilvington Grammar and St. Kevins Primary. Superb finishes, a key focus on subtle details, Spotted Gum timber floors and high ceilings define a formal lounge and an open plan family/meals domain that incorporates a sleek stone kitchen with breakfast bar and quality SMEG appliances. Living areas merge outside to a stunning blue stone paved courtyard generously accommodating for outdoor gatherings and entertaining. 4 robed bedrooms are zoned upstairs and include a main with walk-in robe and luxurious ensuite and are accompanied by 2 fully tiled stone bathrooms. Impeccably equipped with ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, beautifully crafted timber staircase, landscaped front garden, water tank and double lock-up garage.

Character-Filled Californian with Charm & Convenience!
Bringing luxury to everyday living, this charming Californian Bungalow offers authentically detailed period perfection, sympathetically updated & extended to suit the modern al-fresco entertainer. Description:
Solid Ormond Beauty in the Zone
Zone in on solid family living at a sought-after McKinnon College address. A showpiece of its era extended from a solid-brick base to offer modern family accommodation, this original AVJennings home features great late period detail and generous five bedroom, two bathroom accommodation.
Oriented to north sun with a grand and gracious lounge with an impressive marble fireplace and a fifth bedroom (big enough to double as another living-room), this inviting home features a full dining-room beside a modern Ilve appliance kitchen and well-designed bathrooms!
Centrally heated with reverse-cycle air-conditioning and built-in robes, there's a wealth of Deco-style detail including curvaceous cabinetry and a fitted sofa (with hidden storage!) and great (approx) 6600sqft/613sqm grounds with plentiful parking including two-car auto-garage. Ormond addressed, McKinnon College Zoned and located on the bus-route to the tram, station, bay and Monash University, this is a true Zone beauty!

Description:
Relaxing, low maintenance living
One of a pair but on its own land, this solid-brick period home offers solid value to owner-occupiers or investors. With some attractive period features remaining - such as ornamental ceilings and cornices as well as picture rails in a number of rooms - the home has neutral toned paintwork to make a light bright interior, polished hardwood flooring, a stylishly renovated kitchen (gas cooking; tiled splashbacks), a modernised bathroom (separate toilet) and contemporary amenities such as ducted heating. The spacious living room has an open fireplace. Both bedrooms are well proportioned, with the master bedroom having mirror-fronted built-in wardrobes. At the rear of the house there is a wide, partially covered deck (great for alfresco relaxing or entertaining) set in a private garden. Among the inclusions are a separate laundry, off-street parking, and a shed. This low maintenance property is in strolling distance of Kilvington, reserves, local shops, buses, trains, recreation and cafes.

Description:
A Light Filled Original with Garden Appeal
First time offered is this immaculately maintained 3 bedroom street front villa is a fantastic starter, renovator or investment in this sought after pocket.
Invitingly spacious with beautiful north-west light filtering in, this heart-warming treasure features a security door entry, expansive living & dining room, kitchen/meals, 3 double bedrooms (2 with BIRs), central bathroom, powder room and a large laundry.
With private use of an established front garden and side courtyard, this lovely home features ducted heating, a R/C air conditioner, external blinds, a double auto garage + visitors parking.
In a small group of three, a stones throw to North Road shops, cafes and restaurants, the Monash University bus, Ormond station, schools and glorious parkland.

Description:
Space & comfort in a convenient locale
The rear one of two peacefully picturesque residences, this delightful home is spacious, well presented, and sun-filled, delivering a restful, low maintenance lifestyle that will appeal to a variety of buyers. The home has an entrance foyer into a large living room (with extensive glazing, a ceiling fan and timber venetians) open to an expansive modern kitchen (A/C) with dining area. There are 3 bedrooms - all with ceiling fans and built-in wardrobes. A deck and private garden make a pleasant outdoor entertaining area. Extras include polished timber floors; ducted heating; automatic door on the carport (which could be an undercover alfresco area); shed. The leafy location is next to reserves and recreation, and near North Road shops, cafes and train station as well as buses, schools and more.

Description:
Classic Californian on 664sqm/7,140sqft (approx.)!
Always popular, this timeless brick Californian Bungalow is character-filled & fresco-focused. Stepping beyond a welcoming, deep, tuck-pointed verandah you'll discover a charming family home offering a wide fretworked entry, formal lounge & dining, three robed bedrooms & an updated deluxe bathroom with suspended vanity...all wrapped with high ornate ceilings, deep window ledges & stunning leadlight! A central skylit kitchen (stainless-steel stove & timber bench tops) & air-conditioned family room (hardwood floors) opens out to sunny westerly-orientated gardens for indoor/outdoor undercover entertaining amid meandering brick pathways, established gardens & a cubby for the kids. With EE Gunn Reserve at one end of the street, Ormond's shopping strip & station at the other, and neighboured by quality period properties protected by a Heritage overlay, you'll enjoy this quiet residential locale for years to come. Heating, shed, solar HWS, alarm & double carport on 664sqm/7,140sqft (approx.).

Description:
Executive Pad or a Brilliant Start
Situated just moments to the bustle of Ormond village with shopping, cafs, eateries, station and amenities, this executive ground-floor apartment flaunts designer living at its best delivering an enviable lifestyle pad ideal for homebuyers entering into the property market, downsizers and professionals alike. A bright and inviting free-flowing layout boasts an expansive living and dining area enjoying sliding doors opening out to the undercover paved patio and tidy courtyard with entry direct to Grange Road with bus transport. The sophisticated kitchen sparkles with stainless-steel appliances (oven, gas cooktop, range hood and dishwasher) and is beautifully appointed with a waterfall island bench with breakfast bar flaunting solid Caesar stone surfaces plus a large pantry and wine rack. The inviting bedroom is fitted with mirrored robes and serviced by the ultra-chic bathroom with discreet European laundry. A powder room, split-system heating and cooling, a private underground car space, storage cage and security entrance finishing ideally. Positioned close to trams, parklands and walking trails, Carnegie Swim Centre, Caulfield Racecourse, and just a ten-minute drive to Brighton Beach, this fabulous inner-suburb apartment is sure to be coveted. Act fast and enquire today!
- Elegant and stylish one-bedroom apartment
- Open plan living and meals with access to patio and courtyard
- Sparkling kitchen showcasing stone surfaces and stainless appliances
- Mirrored robes, powder room, ultra-chic bathroom and European laundry
- Split-system, secure car space and storage cage, close to amenities
